sols_latex:
Since the bacterial culture grows at a rate proportional to its size, we
can say that $\frac{dy}{dt} = ky$, where $\displaystyle y(t)$ is the
number of bacteria at time $\displaystyle t$ (in hours).

The solution to this differential equation is:\\$\displaystyle y(t) = y(0)e^{kt}$\\\\ We are given that $\displaystyle y(0) = 50$ and
$\displaystyle y(1) = 250$, so we can solve for $\displaystyle k$ as
follows:

\begin{align*}
y(1) &= y(0)e^{k\cdot1}
\\ 250 &= 50e^k
\\ 5 &= e^k
\\ k &= \ln5
\\
\\ \therefore y(t) &= 50e^{\ln(5)t}
\\ &= {\color{blue} 50 \cdot 5^t}
\end{align*}

